nd J. of P.\nby Ame Hillyer, our talented legal light\nAn addishion built onto his kitchen\nBradbury.\nFront palings repaired by Deacon\nbuilder.\nbam by Lem Brown, our carpenter and\nNew grain bin in Doc Livermore\u2019s\nby Hez Andrews.\nHen house, 6 x 9, if boards hold out,\ning list, viz, towit\ngivin in this eonneckshion the follow\nbe built, and we take grate pleasure in\npose of findin out jest whot it going to\nthe interests of the Bugle for the pur\na house to house canvas tother day in\ncompleshion without delay. We made\nwill be pushed rapidly forward fords\nand now the weather is gettin better\ning ip our midst wich has been laid out\nthink else, is the large amount of build\nof this boom, perhaps more than enny\nOne thing that indicates the growth\nis coming true.\nit had time enuff. Our prophetic words\nCo. seat) would grow and prosper if\n(being as it is only 15 miles from the\nness to civilisashion, as you might :.ay\nto its natural advantages and its near\nollus sed however that Bingville, owing\nare much pleased to note it. We have\nyeer of all yeers, but nevertheless we\ntribute this boom to. espeshially this\ncountry. We don\u2019t know whot to at\nwith other populous centers thruout the\nhelp this town take her place erlong\nwill do more than ennythink else to\nwill be far reaching in its effeck and\nthat this is a presidential year, wich\nboom this spring, in spite of the faekt\ndicate that Bingville will be on the\nThere is menny indicashions wich in\nAn Apology\nIt Is with deep regret we haft to send\nout thla week\u2019s Bugle with our editorial\nsomewhat mixed up and natchurally our\narmy of readers will look for a sxplana\nshlon somers In the paper and so here It\nIs:\nLast Friday morning BUI Hepburn come\nInto our offlse and sed he had to make a\nspeshlal trip to the Co. seat to get some\nbolts and supplies and ast us to accom\npany him. We accepted the Invite with\ngrate cheer, being as we have beea atlckln\nparty close to work this winter and went\nwith Bill. At the Co. seat we met sev\neral old friends at five or six different\nplaces and after dinner Bill hitched up\nand we started for Blngvtlle. On the\nway Bill he linkered up and before we\nreached Teck's HIU he managed to throw\nus out of the buggy twice while he sot\nIn the waggon and laffed lit to bust.\nWhen we Anally reached Blngvllle at I\no'clock Bill went to his shop while we\nunlocked our offlse and went to work. We\nwas that tired from riding In Bill's rick\nety old waggon that we could hardly walk\nand stept on the offlse cat with one foot\nand Into the ssh pan with the other be\nfore we got our coat off. Then we tried\nto take our boots off without using our\nboot Jack and we lost our balunce and\ntipped the paste pot all over us. By that\ntime our head begin to ache so bad we\ncould scalrsly see whot we was doing\nwhen we set our editorial, and begun\nat the bottom and set It all up back\nend to, as you might say. As we\nbroke our specs when we fell we\ncouldn't see this until we went to\npress and It was too late for us to change\nand git the Bugle out this week. As for\nBUI he ort to be ashalmed of hlsself for\nglttlng drunk when he has a respectful\nfeller townsman with him and editorially\nspeakln we will never again go to the Co.\nseat with a man that drinks strong llcker\n\u2014not by a Jugful.\nPersonals\nSlme Peters had occashion to look Into\none of his bee hives the other day. and\nto his turrlble disgust he found that all\nhis bees was froze dead. Slme sed he\ndidn't dream It was slch a cold winter we\nhad went through.\nHen Weathersby. prop, of our general\nstore, has receeved a stock of ladles\u2019\nstockings wlch he ordered for last fall\nand sold two pr. right off to Phoebe Hll\nderbrand who brought them back the next\nday. Phoebe sed they looked long enuff,\nbut when she put them on it made them\ntoo short for her.\nMiss Jane McCrackln Is havin a new\ndress cut out by her mother. Unless It\nflts Jane better than the last one her\nmother made for her. we feel sorry for\nJane, for that last dress caused a good\neal of talk around town.\nMrs. Cy Hoskins went to the CO. seat\nlast week and bought a bar! of flour and\na big box of groceries and the next day\nCy went Into Hen tVeathersby\u2019e and paid\nHen the bal, of whot he owed him. Cy\nsed he saved that much on his goods by\ngettln them In a lump. Hen says he Is\nglad to get Ills money, but that alnt no\nway to paternlse home trade.\nMrs. Martha Tucker Is now able to get\nout and talk with the nabers after being\nhoused In all winter with a bunyan on\nher right foot. She cut a hole In her\nshoe so her toe Joint could stick out and\nnow enjoys every steps she takes.\nThe Blngville church needs painting\nawful bad. The Deacons talked some of\npainting It last fall, but somehow or oth\ner they didn't get around to It.\nIsrael Goodwin, more familiar knowd\nas \u2018Tz.\" caught his hand In a glass Jar\nat the store Satterday night while tryln\nto flsh out a twisted peppermint stick and\nhad to smash same before he got It out\nI\nA* we so to press Snake Crick, wlcb\npasses through our midst la on Its regu\nlar spring rampage and Is rising at the\nrate of two Inches a hour. It commenced\nlast Wednesday to swell up following the\nthaw wlch set In a few days ago meltln\nthe snow In the mountings and has grad\nually Increased In volume until the crick\nIs running over In some places. If them\nof you don't get the Bugle next week or\nthe week after you will know that Our\nprinting offlce is warshed often the map\nand that like as not we have got wet to\nthe skin sailing around on a bam door\nand died of ttephoyd fever or some\nthink similar.\nErbout a hour ago Abe Whlttacre called\nat the Bugle offlse to tell us that Hame\nWilson who lives right on the crick\nmoved out this morning owing to the\nfackt that his wife objeckted to wadln\naround In water two ft. deep In order\nto do her house work and dust off the\nfurniture. Hame Intended to move out\nennyhow erbout May 1st. but being as\nthe watter has rlx so rapidly he mooved\nsooner. Hame's household goods and per\nsonnel chattels, as you might say, Is now\non top of Teck's Hill where Hame thinks\nthey will be safe for a few days at\nleast\nRanse Smiley, who also lives close to\nthe crick is now living In the seckoned\nstory of bis house. Ranse has a boat\nand says he is going to stick to his\nhouse as long as there Is enny of It In\nsight above watter. All his hens and a\npig Is In one room up stairs and Ranse\ngot enulf eggs for breakfast this morn\ning to pay for the trouble of carting them\nup there.\nRome of our most respectful cltlsens\nhave packed up their goods and are\nreddy to move If the watter comes up\nmuch higher.\nLATER\u2014Cy Hoskins was Jest 1n and\nhe says he thinks the flood Is subsiding,\nbut as a precaushionary move he has\nordered the Snake Bend saw mill to\nstart up full force to use up as much\nsurplus watter as possible, and thinks\nBlngvllle will exscape with the loss of\nonly one hen house and several old\ncbickhen coops.\nLank Spiled It\nMrs. Jerushy Perkins left a mountain\nof coffee Jelly and cream on our dean\nlaat week and receeved our thanks. We\nwas purty blzzy at the time and didn't\nthink ennythlnk more erbout It until\nLank Jones ast us whot In tarnashlon\nhe had sot on. We looked up. and to our\nhorror and disgust there was our Jelly\nand cream plastered all over the seat of\nhis pants with the sawser bruk In erbout\n17 pieces and still clinging to him. We\ninvited Lank to clear out before we lost\nour temper and the last we see of him he\nwas scrapln hlsself on the palings of Cy\nHoskins' fence.\nSchool Closed Thursday\nThe short wood In the Blngvllle school\nhouse shed Is being used by some low\ndown theef that's too blamed lazy to\ntake the long sticks and saw them, and\nJed Peters, our Intellijent school teacher,\nhad to close school )^st Thursday op .that\nacct. Jed and some of the schollars then\nsawed enuff to last the bal. of the week\nand piled It up In the school room under\nlock and key. Hank Dewberry heard er\nbout it down to the store and told ths\nselectmen that he had erbout 4 chords\nof wood that hs had sawed up In hla\nspare time, this winter, that he would\nsell cheep, and tha aalactmen bought\nthree cords often him so that ths school\ncan keep open until vacashlon.\nlocals\nMIm Phoebe Hllderbrand. our talented\ndressmaker, has returned from a 2 days'\nvisit to the County seat with large\nsupply of patterns she bought at a clos\ning out sale at a little store that had\nbeen In business forty yeers. Ennyone\nwhet wants a new Easter basque or pol\nonaise made must call at once, as she\nexpeckta to be turrtble Mxzy.\nHeck Barclay haa jest got rid of a boll\non hla neck and now hat anuther one\neofnln. This la the fourth boll Heck haa\nhad since the first of the month. He says\nIt la gettin to be turrlble monotonous\nwith him.\nDave White, our popular undertaker,\nhas told the boys of the Blngville Horn\nSand that they could use hla shop to\npracktlse Id until business picks up this\nspring.\nBud in Trouble (gain\nBud Hinckley, who alnt quite right In\nhis head, while playing hide and look\ntot her day, got Into a flour barl and\ncouldn't get out until hla mother chopped\nthe hoops often It. Bud he was awful\nskeard at first but when he got out he\njest erbout laifed hlsself to deth until\nMrs. Hinckley got mad and whaled him\nfor makln slch a fool of hlsself.\nCountry Correspondence\nFLINCHVILLE.\nBill Hendrick's wife of Zion Crossroad*\nwho has been vissitln Mrs. Ransom Tay\nlor. terminated her visit ruther sudden\nyesterday morning and has returned home\nfor an indefinite stay.\nJeremy Hooker druv to the Co. seat\nlast week with a load of shook. He done\nseveral errunds for the nabers and come\nhome with a purty good load.\nMiss Lucinda Watkins had the earache\nthe other day erbout 4 a. m., but Is much\nbetter as we write this.\nEben Williams who is workln over at\nSnake Bend spent Sunday at home.\nMiss Rose Snyder, the bell of Fllach\nvllie, attended a theatre show at the Co.\nseat last week, and Is now thinking some\nof going on the stage to sing and dance\nher way to fame and forchune. If she\ndoes, she will leave one sad heart be\nhind, won't she, Hiram?\nTour correspondent expeckts to get a\nnew subscriber next week and has almost\nclosed the dicker. The party wants sam\nple copies for three mos. and we are hold\ning out for two. LIBERTY.\nELDERBERRY GAP.\nAdam Cutler vissited Hardscrabble last\nweek and bought a half bushel of clams.\nHans Dorfilnger while dressing a steer\nhad the knife to slip and cut two fingers.\nHans was awful surprised but took It\ngood natured being as the fingers was on\na nuther feller's hand who was helptn\nhim.\nRebecca Sprlgglns has had to let out\nthe seams in her Sunday dress she's git\ntin that stout. Nine years makes quite\na different* In a person's stoutness or\nthinness, as you might say.\nSeth Dobbins, who has shaved hlsself\nall winter and put 6 eta In a china apple\nbank each time, broke the bank tother\nday and found 11.13. Seth say* he must\nof cheated hlsself outen 2 cts. some time\nor other.\nSnide Emmons had a flare-up with Mll\nly Hobbs Wednesday night on acct of\nHank Sklhner askln her to go to a party\nwith him. Snide didn't find It out until\nthe next night after she went.\nLtge Simmons druv to the Co. seat last\nTuesday and bought a pr of whot he call*\npegtop pants. He looks like a bottle bug\nIn them.\nAndrew White while makin some hot\nginger tea for his cold yesterday had the\nkettle to slip on him and spill some boil\ning watter on hi* feet Only for his cow\nhides he migh* have been burned to doth.\nSIC SEMPER TRYANN.\nBeery spring 1 hold Mg ul\u00ab a* good* whteB\nI Have Had in Stock\nfor Five or Ten.\nYears Back\nand dnd I make non money Ota wag thaa t\ndo by doling good* oat\nIn Small Massac\nand charging them up\nJed Peter* took inventory for me tkte Wtata*\nand went or or my atoek of good* and tided *p\nIn toy allow case and\nsays he was sur\nprised to see whot\na nise line of goods\ni had stored away\nThey constat of big bargain* ha t\nFur Caps\nFur Coats\nMitts, Boots\nHeavy Wool\nUnderware\nand other good* wklch 1 will anil cheep la oMgg\nto git abet of thorn and tha\nMoths Which ot Several\nMeals Oltfeo Them\nSale Begins Next Monday\nend Will Last all the\nWeek or Longer\nTOTJR8 FOR BARGAINS\nHEN WEATHERSBY\nBingellle. Prop. BtngrUlo Oeo. Store.\nFOOAlL\nBeinjj aa I h*y* decided to qwlt ropatrtng\nfan going to aalUf alt air tools aad\nfor wich I will take TS cents. There la no\nsinner In tb* naibrella Bitng bLantss In Blag\netllr. and\nI don\u2019t think TB eta. ta too aaaek fop\na good opening in this liaa\nBee ate about this oSar before It la grabd ap.\nIKE DOOUTTUB.\nUmbrella BBUkS\nBiagrllla.","height":"27512","width":"19840"}}
